sql:
SELECT access_count
FROM data_reports
WHERE report_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS report_count
FROM data_reports
WHERE generated_by = 1;

SELECT MAX(value) AS max_pollutant_value
FROM environmental_data
WHERE geoid = '1';

SELECT AVG(value) AS average_value
FROM environmental_data
WHERE pollutant_id = 0 AND timestamp = '2023-04-30';

SELECT geoid, MAX(timestamp) AS latest_timestamp
FROM environmental_data
GROUP BY geoid;

external_knowledge:
The top 3 most sought-after locations refers to the locations with the highest total accesses; 
The overall access frequencies refer to the sum of total_accesses for each location; 
The average session lengths refer to the average duration of access sessions for each location; 
The most common ways they are accessed refer to the most frequent access types for each location.

